cocky's joy
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:golden syrup or treacle
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:bullocky's joy
Pronunciation:
Notes: c1940 at least Mrs N.Ngatai: fide p.c. Helen Small 1986 Mar 3 [golden syrup]  [cf Simpson Sugarbag Years 64 informant speaks of cocky's joy as G. Syrup and fried scones : Mrs Ngatai mentions fried scones as well] Also as cocky's delight (no cit.)
